I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Berkshire Refrigerated Warehousing, LLC (Berkshire) facility located at 4550 South Packers Avenue in Chicago, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This 5-year, updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    Berkshire policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Response Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Berkshire Refrigerated Warehousing, LLC Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Berkshire; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Berkshire is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Berkshire policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations. 



